mmary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test setup requirements**\\n\\nI'm looking at the issue with native-image run failures for existing tests. It seems there may not be a need for a new library, but maybe an optional dependency for OAuth2WebClient could provide meaningful coverage. I wonder if the setup should include `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2:5.0.1`. The current build has specific system properties for 5.0.0, so running into trouble with 5.0.1 could be a problem. Should I just choose no_action unless there's clear evidence for more setup?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Netty setup for Java 25**\\n\\nThe normal test scaffold doesn’t set the Netty Java 25 native flags, which is a bit of a concern. I might need to check the documentation for reference. While a local Gradle run with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=...` could verify dependencies, it could be heavy and modify the build. The user says not to apply any setup, but I might inspect the repo metadata for version 5.0.0 since failure seems linked to absent system properties. Adjusting for version 5.0.1 might help, especially concerning runtime options for native images.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 is normal in-process HTTP client usage and does not require Docker or extra dependencies for core coverage, but it still resolves Netty 4.2.x and needs the same Java 25 native-run system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native test runtime, set system properties/runtime args `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true` for 5.0.1. Core meaningful coverage can use `Vertx.vertx()`, `WebClient`, and a local `HttpServer` on `127.0.0.1`; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Optional APIs such as OAuth2 WebClient or POJO JSON mapping may require optional Vert.x/Jackson dependencies, but core WebClient coverage is reachable without adding them.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and native-image verification remain authoritative; the native-run failure may expose additional metadata needs after the Netty/JDK 25 runtime properties are applied.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04898e4662f00453016a3f4a4342c88195a32a1760a01cc68e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3686, "output": 1294, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33652, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782532661034, "responseId": "resp_04898e4662f00453016a3f4a357cec8195aed8c16ae367ba60"}}
